<h2>Chapter 2: Probability</h2>

<h3>Definition of Probability</h3>
<p>Probability measures the likelihood of an event occurring.</p>

<h3>Types of Events</h3>
<p>Events can be simple, compound, independent, dependent, mutually exclusive, or exhaustive.</p>

<h3>Addition & Multiplication Rules</h3>
<p>These rules calculate probabilities of combined events.</p>

<h3>Conditional Probability</h3>
<p>It measures the probability of an event given another event has occurred.</p>

<h3>Bayes’ Theorem</h3>
<p>Bayes’ theorem updates probabilities using prior knowledge.</p>

